1. Create a thin pool named `mythinpool`
2. Create file `/etc/microshift/lvmd.yaml`:
   ```
   socket-name: /run/lvmd/lvmd.sock
   device-classes:
   - name: ssd-thin
     default: true
     volume-group: rhel
     type: thin
     thin-pool:
       name: mythinpool
       overprovision-ratio: 10.0
   ```
3. Build MicroShift: `$ make`
4. Run Microshift: `sudo _output/bin/microshift run` and wait until all pods are ready
5. Run `minio` on microshift's host, tweak `3sUrl` in `30-dpa.yaml`, create bucket `oadp`
6. Run `cd oadp-test && ./0000.sh`
7. After pod is running run: `oc create -f ./60-backup.yaml`
8. Check backup for completion: `oc get -n openshift-adp backup test -o yaml` - phase should be `Completed` and minio's bucket should have dir `velero` with `test` dir inside
